cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on improving object recognition in visual systems using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new activation function for managing bias shift in CNNs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training the parameterization of the activation function, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
